(define Main-helpText (PreludeC-45Types-u--foldMap_Foldable_List csegen-38 (lambda (eta-0) eta-0) (cons "idris2-evm - Pure Idris2 EVM Interpreter\xa;\xa;USAGE:\xa;  idris2-evm-run [options] <bytecode-file>\xa;  idris2-evm-run --bytecode 0x600160... [options]\xa;\xa;DESCRIPTION:\xa;  Executes EVM bytecode through a pure Idris2 interpreter.\xa;\xa;  When this tool is compiled with Idris2's --coverage flag, the Chez Scheme\xa;  profiler tracks which interpreter branches are executed. This gives\xa;  semantic coverage of your EVM/Yul code mapped back to Idris2 functions.\xa;\xa;OPTIONS:\xa;  -h, --help              Show this help message\xa;  -v, --version           Show version\xa;  --verbose               Verbose output (show each step)\xa;  -d, --disassemble       Disassemble bytecode and exit\xa;  --gas <limit>           Gas limit (default: 1000000)\xa;  --calldata <hex>        Calldata as hex (e.g., 0x371303c0)\xa;  --bytecode <hex>        Bytecode as hex (alternative to file)\xa;\xa;EXAMPLES:\xa;  # Execute bytecode file with calldata\xa;  idris2-evm-run --calldata 0x371303c0 contract.bin\xa;\xa;  # Execute inline bytecode (Counter increment)\xa;  idris2-evm-run --bytecode 0x60016000540160005500 --calldata 0x\xa;\xa;  # Disassemble bytecode\xa;  idris2-evm-run -d contract.bin\xa;\xa;INTEGRATION WITH COVERAGE:\xa;  To collect coverage data, rebuild with --coverage:\xa;    idris2 --cg chez --coverage src/Main.idr -o idris2-evm-run\xa;\xa;  Then run the interpreter. The Chez .ssi files will contain hit counts\xa;  for each branch in the interpreter, reflecting which EVM opcodes\xa;  were executed.\xa;\xa;SUPPORTED OPCODES:\xa;  - Arithmetic: ADD, MUL, SUB, DIV, MOD, EXP, etc.\xa;  - Comparison: LT, GT, EQ, ISZERO, etc.\xa;  - Bitwise: AND, OR, XOR, NOT, SHL, SHR, etc.\xa;  - Memory: MLOAD, MSTORE, MSTORE8\xa;  - Storage: SLOAD, SSTORE\xa;  - Control: JUMP, JUMPI, JUMPDEST, STOP, RETURN, REVERT\xa;  - Stack: POP, PUSH0-PUSH32, DUP1-DUP16, SWAP1-SWAP16\xa;  - Environment: CALLER, CALLVALUE, CALLDATALOAD, etc.\xa;  - Block: NUMBER, TIMESTAMP, CHAINID, etc." '())))
